Freakonomics is a study of bizarre, mundane and exceedingly interesting questions. It employs the arsenal of mathematical sophistication to unearth truths and secrets that are hidden from plain sight.

In the book &ldquo;Siddhartha&rdquo; by Herman Hesse – the protagonist, who is a Samana (a homeless hermit), is enchanted by the beauty of a woman named Kamala. On their first discourse, Kamala asks him what is he capable of doing that he can trade for money, pretty clothes, shoes, sweet perfumes and gifts for her. To which Siddhartha replies,
&ldquo;I can think. I can wait. I can fast.&rdquo;
I think that is a very profound answer and it will do ignorant fools like us much good if we make an attempt to comprehend it.
